                - text: "Perfect! I have all the information needed. Here's a comprehensive summary of the team-related routes and endpoints in the Go backend:\n\n## Summary of Routes and Endpoints\n\n### 1. **Team Routes (Registered in routes.go, lines 106-116)**\n\n```go\n// Team (current user's team — matches Next.js frontend endpoints)\nprotected.Get(\"/team\", teamHandler.MyTeam)\nprotected.Patch(\"/team\", teamHandler.UpdateMyTeam)\nprotected.Get(\"/team/members\", teamHandler.MyTeamMembers)\n\n// Teams (multi-team API)\nteams := protected.Group(\"/teams\")\nteams.Get(\"/\", teamHandler.List)\nteams.Post(\"/\", teamHandler.Create)\nteams.Get(\"/:id\", teamHandler.Show)\nteams.Post(\"/:id/invite\", teamHandler.Invite)\n```\n\n### 2. **Team Handler Methods (teams.go)**\n\nThe TeamHandler defines these methods:\n- **List**: `GET /api/teams` - Lists all teams the user is a member of\n- **Create**: `POST /api/teams` - Creates a new team\n- **Show**: `GET /api/teams/:id` - Gets a specific team by ID\n- **MyTeam**: `GET /api/team` - Returns the user's first/primary team with member count\n- **UpdateMyTeam**: `PATCH /api/team` - Updates the current team (owner/admin only)\n- **MyTeamMembers**: `GET /api/team/members` - Lists all members of the user's team\n- **Invite**: `POST /api/teams/:id/invite` - Invites a user to a specific team by email\n\n### 3. **Invite Endpoint Details (teams.go, line 223)**\n\n```go\n// Invite handles POST /api/teams/:id/invite\nfunc (h *TeamHandler) Invite(c fiber.Ctx) error {\n    // POST body: { \"email\": \"user@example.com\", \"role\": \"member\" | \"admin\" | \"owner\" }\n    // Requires owner or admin role\n    // User must exist in the database already\n    // User cannot already be a team member\n}\n```\n\n### 4. **Project Creation Endpoint**\n\n**Route**: `POST /api/projects` (projects.go, line 70)\n```go\n// Create handles POST /api/projects\n// Request body: { \"name\": \"string\", \"description\": \"string\", \"team_id\": \"string|null\" }\n// Returns 201 Created with the new project object\n```\n\n### 5. **Note Creation Endpoint**\n\n**Route**: `POST /api/notes` (notes.go, line 40)\n```go\n// Create handles POST /api/notes\n// Request body: { \n//   \"title\": \"string\", \n//   \"content\": \"string\", \n//   \"project_id\": \"string|null\", \n//   \"team_id\": \"string|null\", \n//   \"pinned\": bool \n// }\n// Returns 201 Created with the new note object\n```\n\n## Key Files\n\n- **Routes**: `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/web/internal/routes/routes.go`\n- **Team Handler**: `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/web/internal/handlers/teams.go`\n- **Project Handler**: `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/web/internal/handlers/projects.go`\n- **Note Handler**: `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/web/internal/handlers/notes.go`\n\nAll routes require authentication (protected by middleware.Auth middleware)."
