        last_assistant_message: "Perfect! I now have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive summary of the Linux build system and dependencies.\n\n## Summary: Orchestra Linux Desktop App — Build System & Dependencies\n\nThe Linux app (currently a planned/documented artifact) does not exist yet in the repository, but there is a comprehensive architectural specification in **`/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/docs/artifacts/21-linux-desktop-app.md`**.\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Build System**\n\n**Meson** (GNOME standard build system)\n- Root config: `apps/linux/meson.build` \n- Build options: `meson_options.txt` (profiles, QUIC backend selection)\n- Two main libraries: `orchestra-kit/` and `shared/`\n- Sub-project for desktop app entry point: `desktop/`\n- Compilation target: valac (Vala compiler) → C → GCC/Clang → native binary\n\n**Build command pattern:**\n```bash\nmeson setup builddir\nmeson compile -C builddir\nmeson install -C builddir\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Core Dependencies**\n\n| Library | Version | Purpose | Type |\n|---------|---------|---------|------|\n| **GTK4** | >= 4.12 | UI toolkit | Required |\n| **libadwaita** | >= 1.4 | GNOME adaptive widgets (NavigationSplitView, etc.) | Required |\n| **Vala** | >= 0.56 | Compiler (Vala → C) | Required (dev) |\n| **GLib** | >= 2.76 | GObject system, event loop, data structures | Required |\n| **GtkSourceView 5** | >= 5.10 | Code editor with syntax highlighting | Required |\n| **VTE 4** | >= 0.74 | Terminal emulator (DevTools) | Required |\n| **libsecret** | >= 0.20 | Credential storage (GNOME Keyring/KDE Wallet) | Required |\n| **ngtcp2** | >= 1.2 | QUIC transport (C library) | Required |\n| **GnuTLS** | >= 3.8 | mTLS/TLS for QUIC | Required |\n| **protobuf-c** | >= 1.5 | Protobuf serialization (wire protocol) | Required |\n| **json-glib** | >= 1.8 | JSON parsing | Required |\n| **libsoup 3** | >= 3.4 | HTTP client (updates, API calls) | Required |\n| **sqlite3** | >= 3.40 | Local data cache | Required |\n| **gtk4-layer-shell** | >= 1.0 | Wayland overlay windows (Bubble mode) | Required |\n| **libappindicator3** | >= 12.10 | System tray icon | Optional |\n| **GStreamer 1.0** | >= 1.22 | Audio pipeline (voice TTS/STT) | Required for voice |\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Build Configuration Files**\n\n```\napps/linux/\n├── meson.build                           # Root config\n├── meson_options.txt                     # Options (quic-backend: ngtcp2 or quiche)\n├── orchestra-kit/meson.build             # Core library\n├── shared/meson.build                    # UI components\n├── desktop/meson.build                   # App entry point\n├── data/\n│   ├── dev.orchestra.desktop.desktop.in  # .desktop entry (for launchers)\n│   ├── dev.orchestra.desktop.metainfo.xml.in  # AppStream metadata\n│   ├── dev.orchestra.desktop.gschema.xml     # GSettings schema\n│   └── icons/                             # Freedesktop icon names\n├── po/                                    # Translations (gettext)\n├── flatpak/\n│   ├── dev.orchestra.desktop.yml         # Flatpak manifest (primary dist)\n│   └── dev.orchestra.desktop.Devel.yml   # Dev builds\n├── snap/\n│   └── snapcraft.yaml                    # Ubuntu Snap\n├── debian/\n│   ├── control                            # .deb package metadata\n│   ├── rules                              # Build rules (dh + meson)\n│   └── changelog                          # Changelog\n└── scripts/\n    ├── new-linux-plugin.sh               # Plugin scaffold\n    └── build-release.sh                  # Release helper\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **QUIC Backend Options**\n\nThe `meson_options.txt` allows selection between:\n\n1. **ngtcp2** (default) — Reference C QUIC implementation by NGtech\n   - Used in Flatpak manifest examples\n   - Supports GnuTLS (preferred on Linux)\n   - ~1.9 MB compiled size\n\n2. **quiche** — Cloudflare's QUIC implementation (Rust-based C API)\n   - Alternative option (lower adoption on Linux)\n   - Both are pluggable via Vala VAPI bindings\n\nBoth backends:\n- Connect to orchestrator at `localhost:50100`\n- Use mTLS with certs at `~/.orchestra/certs/`\n- Frame messages with length-delimited Protobuf (4-byte BE uint32 + Protobuf bytes)\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Cross-Compilation & Container Builds**\n\n**Flatpak (Primary Distribution)**\n- Completely sandboxed, cross-distro\n- GNOME Platform runtime 46 (provides GTK4, libadwaita, GLib, etc.)\n- Automatically builds ngtcp2, protobuf-c, and other deps inside container\n- Flathub distribution (auto-updates via GNOME Software)\n\n**Standard Linux Builds (deb/rpm/snap)**\n- Use system-provided libraries\n- Debian/Ubuntu: `dpkg-buildpackage` (uses `debian/rules` with Meson)\n- Fedora/RHEL: rpmbuild (uses .spec file with pkg-config checks)\n- Snap: snapcraft (uses snap/snapcraft.yaml with GNOME extensions)\n\n**AppImage**\n- Portable single binary using linuxdeploy\n- Bundles GTK4, libadwaita, and core deps\n- No root required; works on older distros\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Language & Technologies**\n\n- **Primary Language**: **Vala** (compiles to C via `valac`)\n  - Modern syntax (async/await, closures, generics, null-safety)\n  - Compiles to efficient native GObject code\n  - Same language as GNOME Builder, Geary, Shotwell\n  \n- **Plugin System**: Vala interfaces + GObject type system\n  - Each screen is a plugin (ChatPlugin, ProjectsPlugin, NotesPlugin, etc.)\n  - Plugin registry auto-discovers at runtime\n  - Mirrors Swift app and Go framework architecture\n\n- **UI Framework**: GTK4 + libadwaita\n  - AdwNavigationSplitView for sidebar/detail layout\n  - Dark theme by default (deep navy #0a0d14)\n  - Purple accent (#a900ff) for active states\n\n- **Data**: SQLite for local cache + QUIC connection to orchestrator\n  - Cache at `~/.local/share/orchestra/cache.db`\n  - Certs at `~/.orchestra/certs/` (shared with Go plugins)\n  - Config at `~/.config/orchestra/`\n\n- **Serialization**: Protobuf-c (generated from shared `.proto` files)\n  - Same contract as Swift app and Go plugins\n  - Length-delimited framing for QUIC streams\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Can It Build on macOS?**\n\n**Short Answer: Not directly without significant porting.**\n\n**Why not:**\n- **Vala compiler** (`valac`) is available on macOS via Homebrew/Nix, but...\n- **GTK4 + libadwaita** need X11 or Wayland (macOS uses AppKit/SwiftUI)\n- **ngtcp2** would need GnuTLS (no mTLS equiv on macOS without OpenSSL)\n- **XDG paths** don't exist on macOS (uses `~/Library/` instead)\n- **D-Bus** (notifications, secrets, accessibility, portals) doesn't exist on macOS\n- **GStreamer** is available but audio I/O differs from macOS native APIs\n\n**Possible workarounds:**\n1. **Use Flatpak on macOS** — Not supported; Flatpak is Linux-only\n2. **Cross-compile in container** — Run Linux build inside Docker, compile for Linux target\n3. **Use podman/Docker on macOS** — Build Linux binary in VM, but binary only runs on Linux\n4. **GTK on macOS via X11/XQuartz** — Possible but unstable; UI will not be native\n5. **Port to Swift** — Use the existing Swift app (`apps/swift/`) instead — it's the macOS-native equivalent\n\n**Recommended approach for macOS users:**\n- Use **`apps/swift/`** (native SwiftUI app) instead\n- Both apps connect to the same orchestrator + plugins\n- Swift app has native macOS features (Spotlight, Keychain, WidgetKit, etc.)\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Phase-Based Build Plan**\n\nThe artifact defines 6 phases:\n\n| Phase | Features | Timeline | Desktop Env |\n|-------|----------|----------|-------------|\n| **1** | Shell + Chat MVP | Foundation | GNOME |\n| **2** | Projects + Notes | Features | GNOME + KDE |\n| **3** | Developer Tools | Extensibility | All DEs |\n| **4** | Window Modes + Native | Full IDE | All DEs |\n| **5** | AI Awareness + Voice | Intelligence | All DEs |\n| **6** | Packaging + Distribution | Release | All platforms |\n\n**Exit criteria for Phase 1**: Launch app on GNOME, see plugin-driven sidebar, chat with streaming response.\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Key Build Tools Required**\n\nTo build on Linux:\n\n```bash\n# Fedora/RHEL\nsudo dnf install meson vala gcc pkg-config \\\n  gtk4-devel libadwaita-devel gtksourceview5-devel vte-devel \\\n  libsecret-devel ngtcp2-devel gnutls-devel protobuf-c-devel \\\n  json-glib-devel libsoup3-devel sqlite-devel\n\n# Debian/Ubuntu\nsudo apt install meson valac gcc pkg-config \\\n  libgtk-4-dev libadwaita-1-dev gtksourceview-5-dev libvte-2.91-gtk4-dev \\\n  libsecret-1-dev libngtcp2-dev libgnutls28-dev libprotobuf-c-dev \\\n  libjson-glib-dev libsoup-3.0-dev libsqlite3-dev\n\n# Arch\nsudo pacman -S meson vala gtk4 libadwaita gtksourceview5 vte \\\n  libsecret ngtcp2 gnutls protobuf-c json-glib libsoup sqlite\n```\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\nThe Orchestra Linux Desktop App is a **Vala + GTK4 application** using the **Meson build system**. It depends on **15+ core Linux libraries** (GTK4, libadwaita, ngtcp2, etc.) and is distributed via **Flatpak (primary)**, Snap, .deb, .rpm, AppImage, and AUR. It **cannot run on macOS** without major porting; macOS users should use the native Swift app instead. The build system is mature and well-documented, with clear phase-based rollout planned from Phase 1 (MVP chat) through Phase 6 (packaging/distribution)."
        permission_mode: default
