    - event_type: Stop
      session_id: 699c140c-f58a-4c9e-85ef-b3ec2c825fd9
      data:
        cwd: /Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents
        hook_event_name: Stop
        last_assistant_message: |-
            Here's a summary of all the fixes made:

            ## Fixes Applied

            ### 1. Projects/Notes not saving to DB
            **Root cause**: Backend returns a plain array (`[]`), but frontend expected `{ projects: [] }` / `{ notes: [] }`.

            **Fixed in**:
            - [projects/page.tsx](apps/next/src/app/(app)/projects/page.tsx) — handles both `Array` and `{ projects: [] }`
            - [notes/page.tsx](apps/next/src/app/(app)/notes/page.tsx) — handles both `Array` and `{ notes: [] }`

            ### 2. `/projects/:id` → Project not found
            **Root cause**: Backend uses **slug** as the URL param (`/api/projects/:slug`), but the frontend was linking to `/projects/${p.id}` (UUID).

            **Fixed in**:
            - [projects/page.tsx](apps/next/src/app/(app)/projects/page.tsx) — added `slug` to `Project` interface, links now use `p.slug`
            - [projects/[id]/page.tsx](apps/next/src/app/(app)/projects/[id]/page.tsx) — now hits `/api/projects/${slug}/tree` first, handles both wrapped/unwrapped responses

            ### 3. Team nav not visible / can't see team settings
            **Root cause**: `hasTeam = canManageTeam || canInviteMembers` — regular `user` role has neither permission, so team nav was hidden.

            **Fixed in**:
            - [layout.tsx](apps/next/src/app/(app)/layout.tsx) — `hasTeam = !!(team || canManageTeam || canInviteMembers)` — any user with a team sees team nav
            - User dropdown Team link: now shows whenever `team` exists (not just for managers)

            ### 4. Invite members failing
            **Root cause**: Frontend called `POST /api/team/members/invite` but backend route is `POST /api/teams/:id/invite`.

            **Fixed in**:
            - [store/roles.ts](apps/next/src/store/roles.ts) — `inviteMember` now uses `POST /api/teams/${teamId}/invite`

            ### 5. Multi-team support
